When two or more players meet a loss condition in the same state-based-action check, the engine eliminates them **sequentially** and runs the game-over check **after each elimination**. The first elimination sees the other dying player still "alive" and latches `GameOver { winner: Some(other) }`; the second elimination's game-over check early-returns because the result is already set. The engine therefore declares a player who has *also* lost as the **winner**, when CR 104.4a mandates a **draw**.

State-based actions are required to be performed **simultaneously as a single event** (CR 704.3). The engine violates this by interleaving the game-over check between individual eliminations.

The loss check collects all losers, then eliminates them one at a time (`crates/engine/src/game/sba.rs`):

```rust
