If `send` throws, `pendingResolve`/`pendingReject` stay set and `actionPendingChanged(true)` is never cleared, so the UI is stuck "waiting" and the caller awaits a reply that can never arrive. The fire-and-forget senders (concede, emote, ready, spectate, start, ping) also throw on a dead socket.

`PeerSession` already wraps its `send` in try/catch — the WebSocket adapter should match.

### Expected

A failed send should emit an `error` event and, for `submitAction`, clear the pending state and reject — never leave the adapter hanging. Fire-and-forget sends should not throw on a closed socket.

